The paper discusses the impact of limited-capacity links on the performance of cooperative technology in cellular networks. This topic falls under the area of networked systems and communication, which is covered by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves information theory and signal processing, which are covered by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.MM (Multimedia). The study of cooperative techniques in cellular networks is a subfield of control and systems engineering, which is covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of cooperative techniques, which is relevant to the design and optimization of communication networks, covered by cs.COM (Computers and Society).
